June 3, 2008

Cvsget - convenience script to remotely update a read-only CVS source tree
==========================================================================

SUMMARY: The cvsget shell script semi-automates the retrieval of the latest
         source from CVS repositories for many open source development
         projects. Projects currently supported include the following:
           amavis Amaya Ayttm aolserver autoconf ccvs dejagnu enhydra
           enlightenment everybuddy expect faqomatic firebird fltk freetype
           freetype2 ftpascal ft2demos gdb gtk-gnutella hylafax hypermail
           incrtcl interbase interchange interchangedocs jboss jday jetspeed
           KBackup libtiff libtool libwww lxr mozilla mutt opennms openoffice
           openssh php pymilter python quadra roxen rsync rxvt sabtol samba
           tcl tk tclx tmda trn udi vim wine wxPython

REQUIREMENTS: CVS and a Bourne Shell

DOWNLOAD: ftp://ftp2.sco.com/pub/skunkware/src/devtools/cvsget.gz

INSTALLATION: Download and uncompress the cvsget shell script
              For example:
                # wget ftp://ftp2.sco.com/pub/skunkware/src/devtools/cvsget.gz
                # gunzip cvsget.gz

              Edit the cvsget shell script, setting the SRCDIR variable.
              The default setting is /u/src. Change this to the root of 
              your development source tree.
                 # vi cvsget

              Copy the cvsget shell script to a PATH component and make it
              executable. For example:
                # cp cvsget /usr/local/bin/cvsget
                # chmod 755 /usr/local/bin/cvsget

